title: Industrial Policy
new-page: true
is-card: true
on-arrival: industrial_policy_timer += 6; month_actions += 1
view-if: CHP_in_government = 1 and industrial_minister_party = "CHP" and industrial_policy_timer == 0
card-image: img/portraits/TarhanErdem.jpg
tags: govt_affairs, cabinet

= Industrial Policy

Turkey is undergoing a boom in industrial growth assisted by the state in accordance with the import substitution model. In this model the state supports the assembly and manufacturing industries through tariffs against foreign companies and export subsidies for international competitiveness. Favored by the big industry and capitalists, this model also has its opponents in the form of the petty bourgeoisie who feel sidelined compared to their larger counterparts. 

We need to complete the evolution towards an export economy to build an economy resistant to the turbulences in the price of raw materials.

- @industry1: Basic industrialization push.
- @uretim: Divert industrial production away from consumer goods and towards towards capital and assembly products.
- @elektronik: Move towards high-tech products with great margins of profit such as electronics.
- @capacity: Employ workers at the maximum level in the state-owned interprises, KİTs.
- @kobi: Concentrate small and middle sized interprises into cooperatives.
- @kredi: Shift beneficial loans towards exporting big industry.
- @demiryolu: Restart investment for railway construction.
- @root: No change to industrial policy.
- @easy_discard
- @cancel_advisor_action

@industry1
subtitle: -3 budget. This will assist our efforts for our reorientation towards an export economy. 
on-arrival: budget -= 3; industrial_production_index += 10; capitalist_chp += 5; petty_bourgeoisie += 2; growth_modidifer += 1.5; unemployment_modifier -= 0.5; inflation_modifier += 3.5; industryy += 1; economicaction += 0.5; forex_pressure += 4
choose-if: industryy == 0 and budget >= 3
unavailable-subtitle: [? if budget < 3 : We do not have enough budget! ?] [? if industryy == 1 : We have already begun an industrialization push! ?] 

A significant budget is gathered for a final effort to bring our industry to modern standards. Plans are drawn, modern machinery is bought and our nation moves forward in its economic development. 

@uretim
on-arrival: growth_modifier += 0.5; inflation_modifier += 0.8; forex_pressure -= 3; economicaction += 0.25
choose-if: capacityy == 1
unavailable-subtitle: We have not begun an industrialization push yet!

Through incentives and the state planning agency, DPT, we push our factories to focus on assembly and capital products to be sold abroad. This lessens our dependence on the constant flow of foreign currency and increases growth, even though the price of everyday products increases with inflation.

@elektronik
subtitle: -2 budget. 
on-arrival: growth_modifier += 1.5; inflation_modifier += 3; forex_pressure += 4; forex_pressure_drift -= 1; unemployment_modifier -= 0.5; electronicc += 1; industrial_production_index += 5
choose-if: electronicc == 0 and budget >= 2
unavailable-subtitle: [? if budget < 2 : We do not have enough budget! ?] [? if electronicc == 1 : We have already begun an industrialization push! ?] 

As another step of our economic reform we promote the production of tech products with wide margins of profit. 

@capacity
on-arrival: forex_pressure += 1; inflation_modifier -= 1; growth_modifier += 0.4; unemployment_modifier -= 0.8: capacityy += 1; industrial_production_index += 3
choose-if: capacityy == 0
unavailable-subtitle: We are already pushing our employment to the limit!

We maximize our employments in the state-run industries, pushing growth up and unemployment down.  

@kobi
on-arrival: unemployment_modifier -= 0.3; growth_modifier += 0.4; inflation_modifier -= 0.8; capitalist_chp -= 3; petty_bourgeoisie_chp += 3; industrial_production_index += 3

We utilize the state, planning agency, DPT, to promote concentration of smaller businesses in industrial zones. As smaller businesses gather possible rivals for Turkish industrial giant begin to take shape. 

@kredi
choose-if: MSP_in_government == 0
unavailable-subtitle: MSP is the party of the anatolian petty bourgeoisie! They will prevent this action.
on-arrival: growth_modifier += 0.6; inflation_modifier -= 1.5; petty_bourgeoisie_chp -= 4; industrial_production_index += 5

We shift beneficial loans towards exporting industries which tend to be more concentrated and in the hands of the big capital. While this promotes growth, we should be careful not to push our small producers to the brink of financial struggle.

@demiryolu
subtitle: Asphalt highways became the primary mode of transportation as the Turkish economy shifted towards free market policies in the 1950's. Promoting railroads can promote growth and accompany our industrial promotions.
on-arrival: budget -= 1; growth_modifier += 1; inflation_modifier -= 2: demiryoluu += 1; industrial_production_index += 5
choose-if: demiryoluu == 0
unavailable-subtitle: We have already financed expansion of the railroad lines!

Politics expresses itself in many forms, including even in the basic railroads and highways. While the planned economy of the CHP one party era led to a network of railroads connecting the concentrated industrial zones, as a switch towards free market economics happened in the 1950's under Adnan Menderes's tenure, highways and roads were prioritized to connect the many new decentralized interprises. Now that we are beginning direct investments and planning again, railroad expansions can improve our industrialization efforts.
